25|$|As Rebecca and her entourage {{approached}} Abraham's home, they spied Isaac from {{a distance}} {{in the fields of}} Beer-lahai-roi. The Talmud and the Midrash explain that Isaac was praying, as he instituted Mincha, the afternoon prayer. Seeing such a spiritually exalted man, Rebecca immediately dismounted from her camel and asked the accompanying servant who <b>he</b> <b>was.</b> <b>When</b> she heard that this was her future husband, she modestly covered herself with a veil. Isaac brought her into the tent of his mother Sarah, married her, and loved her.|$|E
